# Firebase config is committed on purpose so GitHub Pages deploys with
# credentials attached. Firebase apiKey is exposed to clients by design;
# access control lives in firestore.rules. Domain whitelist in Firebase
# Console (Authentication → Settings → Authorized domains) mitigates abuse.

# OS / editor cruft
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
*.swp
*~
.vscode/
.idea/

# Local dev logs
*.log
firebase-debug.log
firestore-debug.log

# Node / build outputs (unlikely here but harmless)
node_modules/
dist/
